				&quot;Jacks of all trades&quot; are not always to be shunned.  A single bard can make a much bigger difference to a party of six than a third wizzard.  By twisting songs, they can speed healing between fights (saving your cleric's precious mana for when you really need it), speed up mana recovery, make everybody in the party run faster that Spirit of Wolf allows, and improve the effectiveness of the tanks.  Any time I have the opportunity to invite a bard into a pary, I jump at it!
